ZH: 她正在缝一件漂亮的裙子。
EN: She is sewing a beautiful dress.

ZH: 我不太会缝衣服。
EN: I am not very good at sewing clothes.

ZH: 她用针线缝起了裂开的袜子。
EN: She sewed up the torn socks with a needle and thread.

ZH: 她的妈妈每天都在缝布料。
EN: Her mother sews fabric every day.

ZH: 你可以教我怎么缝裙子吗？
EN: Can you teach me how to sew a skirt?

ZH: 她已经缝好了这件外套。
EN: She has sewn this coat.

ZH: 这些洗衣店都提供缝补服务。
EN: These laundromats all offer sewing services.

ZH: 老奶奶用手缝了一条毛巾。
EN: The old lady sewed a towel by hand.

ZH: 她正在缝logo在公司衬衫上。
EN: She is sewing the logo on the company shirt.

ZH: 这位裁缝工匠很擅长缝制西装。
EN: This tailor is very good at sewing suits.

ZH: 妈妈说可以缝个玩具给我。
EN: Mom said she can sew a toy for me.

ZH: 她的祖母教她缝补裤子。
EN: Her grandmother taught her how to sew and patch pants.

ZH: 这台缝纫机已经修好了。
EN: This sewing machine has been repaired.

ZH: 学会缝纫是一项非常有用的技能。
EN: Learning how to sew is a very useful skill.

ZH: 我妈妈教导我怎么缝缀毛衣。
EN: My mom taught me how to sew and mend sweaters.

ZH: 妹妹喜欢用缝纫机缝裙子。
EN: Little sister likes to use sewing machines to sew skirts.

ZH: 我明白怎样缝包了。
EN: I understand how to sew bags now.

ZH: 这些缝制好的衣服质量很高。
EN: The quality of these sewed clothes is very high.

ZH: 裁缝正在缝制一件漂亮的婚纱。
EN: The tailor is sewing a beautiful wedding dress.
